        "notes": "The building was built in 1908-9 for the Royal College of Dental Surgeons. It was home to the Faculty of Architecture, Landscape and Design from 1961 to 2017. It was altered by Kohn and Schnier in the early 2000's. It is currently being renovated by Superkul for a new student centre. The Eric Arthur Gallery was created within this building, opening November 22, 2001. The gallery is dedicated to architecture and design. The Eric Arthur Gallery won an Honourable Mention in the Toronto Architecture and Urban Design Awards in 2003. A new proposal came forward in 2009 to dramatically increase the size of this building, which would see the entire structure sheathed inside another building, and expanded significantly upwards and to the rear.",
